00:10:06,728 --> 00:10:07,895
<i>Why, because they're</i>
<i>you're client?</i>

243
00:10:07,929 --> 00:10:09,163
No, because
they were Jack's client

244
00:10:09,197 --> 00:10:10,598
and now they're my client.

245
00:10:10,632 --> 00:10:11,799
So this is all about you?

246
00:10:11,833 --> 00:10:13,334
- Louis, calm down.
- No, this is all about you.

247
00:10:13,368 --> 00:10:14,568
You know what?
You're the one who gave

248
00:10:14,603 --> 00:10:16,003
Hardman the opening he needed.

249
00:10:16,037 --> 00:10:17,338
- <i>Did you hear what I just said?</i>
<i>- Excuse me?</i>

250
00:10:17,372 --> 00:10:18,706
Yeah, you heard me.
This wouldn't be happening

251
00:10:18,740 --> 00:10:20,107
if you didn't try to suspend me.

252
00:10:20,142 --> 00:10:21,242
After you punched me
in the face.

253
00:10:21,276 --> 00:10:22,343
If you really want
to know who's at fault here,

254
00:10:22,377 --> 00:10:23,477
why don't you take a look
in the mirror?

255
00:10:23,512 --> 00:10:24,945
That's enough.

256
00:10:24,980 --> 00:10:26,647
<i>This is exactly</i>
<i>what Hardman wants.</i>

257
00:10:26,681 --> 00:10:28,783
He's trying to get us
to turn on each other.

258
00:10:28,817 --> 00:10:31,051
Well, the fight is out there,
not in here,

259
00:10:31,086 --> 00:10:33,854
and we have to figure out
who Hardman's target is.

260
00:10:35,223 --> 00:10:36,257
Where the hell are you going?

261
00:10:36,291 --> 00:10:37,558
You're right,
the fight is out there,

262
00:10:37,592 --> 00:10:40,761
but Jack Soloff's in here.

263
00:10:40,796 --> 00:10:42,730
You think it's a good idea
to let him go after Jack?

264
00:10:42,764 --> 00:10:44,498
What's he gonna do?
Make him less on our side?

265
00:10:44,533 --> 00:10:46,333
You're right.

266
00:10:46,368 --> 00:10:48,169
There's more important things
to do here anyway.

267
00:10:48,203 --> 00:10:49,503
Yeah, and number one
on the list

268
00:10:49,538 --> 00:10:51,338
is if you think that Hardman's
really going after

269
00:10:51,373 --> 00:10:53,413
Nader Communications,
then we need to get over there

270
00:10:53,441 --> 00:10:54,608
and warn them.

271
00:10:54,643 --> 00:10:56,377
It's not Nader,
it's McKernon Motors.

272
00:10:56,411 --> 00:10:57,578
It can't be McKernon.
They're too small.

273
00:10:57,612 --> 00:10:58,913
Not since we did
that battery deal.

274
00:10:58,947 --> 00:11:00,014
And I know
what you're gonna say,

275
00:11:00,048 --> 00:11:01,782
"Avery McKernon's estate
still owns too much

276
00:11:01,817 --> 00:11:04,051
of the stock,"
but not anymore.

277
00:11:04,085 --> 00:11:05,085
Who bought it?

278
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:06,153
It doesn't matter
who bought it.

279
00:11:06,188 --> 00:11:07,254
It matters
who the attorney of record is.

280
00:11:07,289 --> 00:11:09,657
- Let me guess, Daniel Hardman.
- Exactly.

281
00:11:09,691 --> 00:11:11,926
Goddamn it.

282
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:13,360
Harvey, what are you doing?

283
00:11:13,395 --> 00:11:14,762
I'm going
to see Dominic Barone.

284
00:11:14,796 --> 00:11:16,730
- Well, then I'm going with you.
- No, you're not.

285
00:11:16,765 --> 00:11:18,065
They're my oldest client,

286
00:11:18,099 --> 00:11:19,533
and this is something
I have to do.

287
00:11:19,568 --> 00:11:21,936
Harvey, this is a client
that you gave to me and Louis.

288
00:11:21,970 --> 00:11:23,304
Yeah, and you were
smart enough

289
00:11:23,338 --> 00:11:24,772
to figure out
they were the target.

290
00:11:24,806 --> 00:11:26,106
Now I need you
to use that brain

291
00:11:26,141 --> 00:11:29,143
to start figuring out
how we're gonna get out of this.

292
00:11:29,177 --> 00:11:30,711
What are you gonna do?

293
00:11:30,745 --> 00:11:32,479
I'm gonna look Dominic Barone
in the eye

294
00:11:32,514 --> 00:11:35,082
and tell him I'm the reason
this is happening.

295
00:11:37,384 --> 00:11:38,818
Jack, I need to talk to you.

296
00:11:39,316 --> 00:11:40,465
You can save your breath,
Louis.

297
00:11:40,501 --> 00:11:41,800
I know what you're here to say.

298
00:11:41,835 --> 00:11:43,268
You're here to tell me
not to go against

299
00:11:43,270 --> 00:11:45,804
your precious
Harvey and Jessica.

300
00:11:45,839 --> 00:11:47,823
No, I'm here to tell you
that you have no idea

301
00:11:47,858 --> 00:11:49,441
who you're in bed with.

302
00:11:49,493 --> 00:11:52,377
Well, I appreciate
your concern for my well-being,

303
00:11:52,412 --> 00:11:55,013
but I can handle myself.
No you can't.

304
00:11:55,048 --> 00:11:56,348
What difference does it make,
Louis?

305
00:11:56,383 --> 00:11:58,283
It's too late.
It's not too late.

306
00:11:58,318 --> 00:11:59,935
You think if
I suddenly abandon Daniel,

307
00:11:59,987 --> 00:12:02,254
Jessica's just gonna welcome
me back with open arms?

308
00:12:02,289 --> 00:12:04,523
Yes, you don't know
how forgiving she can be.

309
00:12:04,558 --> 00:12:06,291
I trust her.
The only thing she's going

310
00:12:06,326 --> 00:12:07,859
to forgive me with
is a knife in the back.

311
00:12:07,911 --> 00:12:09,594
Jack, listen to me.

312
00:12:09,630 --> 00:12:12,497
Daniel Hardman
treated me like a son.

313
00:12:12,533 --> 00:12:14,833
He promoted me
to senior partner,

314
00:12:14,868 --> 00:12:16,334
used me to take over the firm.

315
00:12:16,370 --> 00:12:19,170
After he lost power,
he turns around

316
00:12:19,206 --> 00:12:21,406
and slaps me
with a sexual harassment claim.

317
00:12:21,441 --> 00:12:22,824
I know.
Monica Eaton.

318
00:12:22,860 --> 00:12:25,787
But what you don't know
is that it was bullshit.

319
00:12:28,682 --> 00:12:32,350
He betrayed me.

320
00:12:32,386 --> 00:12:34,986
Humiliated me.

321
00:12:35,022 --> 00:12:36,521
And after I finally
confronted him about it,

322
00:12:36,557 --> 00:12:39,824
he tells me...

323
00:12:39,860 --> 00:12:43,111
that I got
what I always wanted.

324
00:12:43,163 --> 00:12:45,430
So, Jack, believe me,
if you think this man

325
00:12:45,465 --> 00:12:48,533
cares about you, he doesn't.

326
00:12:48,569 --> 00:12:50,168
I know what kind of man
he is, Louis.

327
00:12:50,203 --> 00:12:52,304
Then why are you siding
with him?

328
00:12:52,339 --> 00:12:53,572
I'll tell you why.

329
00:12:53,607 --> 00:12:56,107
He promised to do something
Jessica never would.

330
00:12:56,143 --> 00:12:57,342
Put my name on the wall.

331
00:12:57,394 --> 00:12:59,344
What if she would?

332
00:12:59,379 --> 00:13:00,445
You're not in reality.

333
00:13:00,497 --> 00:13:02,013
Jack, she did it for me.

334
00:13:02,049 --> 00:13:04,282
Even if I wanted
to go with you, I couldn't.

335
00:13:04,318 --> 00:13:06,084
He's got something on you,
doesn't he?

336
00:13:06,086 --> 00:13:07,936
This conversation is over.

337
00:13:17,314 --> 00:13:18,947
Harvey, what the hell?

338
00:13:18,982 --> 00:13:20,448
I just to notification
of a tender offer.

339
00:13:20,484 --> 00:13:21,733
They're coming after
my company.

340
00:13:21,785 --> 00:13:23,034
I know,
that's why I'm here.

341
00:13:23,036 --> 00:13:24,102
So they sent
the big guns to fight

342
00:13:24,137 --> 00:13:25,604
because it's a hostile takeover?

343
00:13:25,639 --> 00:13:27,272
I'm not here
because it's a hostile takeover.

344
00:13:27,324 --> 00:13:29,374
I'm here because
this whole thing is my fault.

345
00:13:29,409 --> 00:13:30,642
What do you mean your fault?

346
00:13:30,694 --> 00:13:31,993
The reason you're
in the crosshairs is because

347
00:13:32,045 --> 00:13:34,379
Daniel Hardman
has a vendetta against me.

348
00:13:34,414 --> 00:13:35,513
You're telling me
we just closed a deal

349
00:13:35,565 --> 00:13:37,582
that ensures
this company's future

350
00:13:37,618 --> 00:13:39,084
and you put it in jeopardy
because you pissed off

351
00:13:39,119 --> 00:13:40,318
your former partner?

352
00:13:40,354 --> 00:13:41,486
Yes, that's
what I'm telling you.

353
00:13:41,521 --> 00:13:43,021
God damn it.

354
00:13:43,023 --> 00:13:44,456
Well what do you
want me to do, Dominic?

355
00:13:44,508 --> 00:13:46,725
I want you to stop being
an asshole to people.

356
00:13:46,760 --> 00:13:48,910
It's too late for that.

357
00:13:48,962 --> 00:13:52,097
But it may not be too late
for this.

358
00:13:52,132 --> 00:13:53,698
Drop us as your attorneys.

359
00:13:53,734 --> 00:13:54,683
What?

360
00:13:54,718 --> 00:13:57,068
As long as
you're connected to us,

361
00:13:57,104 --> 00:13:58,536
there's gonna be
a target on your back.

362
00:13:58,588 --> 00:14:00,605
You let us go,
there's a chance it goes away.

363
00:14:00,657 --> 00:14:01,856
Harvey.

364
00:14:01,908 --> 00:14:03,241
If I was just gonna
cut you loose because

365
00:14:03,276 --> 00:14:04,759
someone hates you,
I wouldn't have hired you

366
00:14:04,795 --> 00:14:07,012
in the fist place,
because we both know

367
00:14:07,047 --> 00:14:09,247
I used to hate you.

368
00:14:09,282 --> 00:14:11,149
Thanks, Dominic.

369
00:14:11,184 --> 00:14:12,851
- So what are we gonna do?
- I'll let you know.

370
00:14:12,886 --> 00:14:14,219
But I'll tell you this:

371
00:14:14,271 --> 00:14:17,022
They want a war,
they got a war.

372
00:14:22,262 --> 00:14:24,062
Hey, Rach, do you have
that Neilson brief for Louis

373
00:14:24,097 --> 00:14:25,096
from last month?

374
00:14:25,098 --> 00:14:26,564
No, I don't.

375
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:27,615
Are you sure?
Because he keeps telling me

376
00:14:27,651 --> 00:14:28,700
that you have it.

377
00:14:28,735 --> 00:14:29,801
And I keep telling him I don't

378
00:14:29,836 --> 00:14:30,802
and I have more
important things to do

379
00:14:30,837 --> 00:14:32,337
than sit around
and answer the same question

380
00:14:32,372 --> 00:14:34,205
every other day.

381
00:14:34,241 --> 00:14:35,874
And I have better things
to do with my time

382
00:14:35,909 --> 00:14:38,309
than to be spoken to that way.

383
00:14:38,345 --> 00:14:40,679
I'm sorry.

384
00:14:40,714 --> 00:14:45,717
Rachel, what's going on?

385
00:14:45,752 --> 00:14:46,851
I just had lunch
with my mom

386
00:14:46,887 --> 00:14:49,754
to talk about our wedding,
and she wants to put

387
00:14:49,790 --> 00:14:51,489
an announcement
in "The New York Times."

388
00:14:51,525 --> 00:14:52,590
Oh, my God.

389
00:14:52,626 --> 00:14:53,658
Did you tell her
that she can't do that?

390
00:14:53,694 --> 00:14:55,160
Yeah.
I made up some story

391
00:14:55,195 --> 00:14:56,678
about it being snobby,
but Donna, that's just

392
00:14:56,713 --> 00:14:57,929
the tip of the iceberg.

393
00:14:57,964 --> 00:14:58,980
What are you talking about?

394
00:14:59,032 --> 00:15:00,865
This is her
proposed guest list.

395
00:15:00,901 --> 00:15:03,234
It is 300 people
and it includes

396
00:15:03,286 --> 00:15:06,938
the Attorney General
and the Dean of Harvard Law.

397
00:15:09,142 --> 00:15:10,392
What am I gonna do?

398
00:15:10,427 --> 00:15:11,493
You're gonna tell her
that you don't want

399
00:15:11,528 --> 00:15:13,178
a big wedding and that's that.

400
00:15:13,213 --> 00:15:14,379
And if I do that,
she's gonna know

401
00:15:14,381 --> 00:15:15,480
that something's not right.

402
00:15:15,482 --> 00:15:17,365
Rachel, this is
the type of argument

403
00:15:17,401 --> 00:15:19,501
that every mother has
with every daughter

404
00:15:19,536 --> 00:15:22,353
about her wedding.

405
00:15:22,389 --> 00:15:25,290
She's never gonna think
that Mike's a fraud.

406
00:15:31,198 --> 00:15:33,231
- How'd Dominic take it?
- He took it fine.

407
00:15:33,266 --> 00:15:34,399
Good, 'cause I have a plan.

408
00:15:34,434 --> 00:15:35,667
Let's hear it.

409
00:15:35,702 --> 00:15:36,634
We go to the last place
they'd ever expect

410
00:15:36,670 --> 00:15:37,836
and we offer to merge.
Where?

411
00:15:37,888 --> 00:15:38,937
Fletcher Engines.

412
00:15:38,972 --> 00:15:40,105
Are you crazy?

413
00:15:40,107 --> 00:15:42,107
We go to Fletcher,
they're gonna kick Dominic out,

414
00:15:42,159 --> 00:15:43,708
Jack gains power.

415
00:15:43,744 --> 00:15:45,076
Might as well have
let McKernon get bought out

416
00:15:45,128 --> 00:15:46,544
in the first place.

417
00:15:46,580 --> 00:15:47,979
Then the only other option
that's even remotely possible

418
00:15:48,031 --> 00:15:50,115
is we take them private.

419
00:15:50,150 --> 00:15:53,151
That actually might work.

420
00:15:53,153 --> 00:15:54,619
Come to think of it,
why the hell didn't you

421
00:15:54,621 --> 00:15:56,087
just say that to me
in the first place?

422
00:15:56,123 --> 00:15:58,556
Because I knew you'd shit on
whatever my first idea was

423
00:15:58,592 --> 00:15:59,891
and that you'd be open
to the backup.

424
00:15:59,926 --> 00:16:01,359
You're telling me
you set up a straw man idea

425
00:16:01,394 --> 00:16:03,595
to manipulate me
into liking your real idea?

426
00:16:03,630 --> 00:16:05,196
- Yep.
- How long you been doing that?

427
00:16:05,232 --> 00:16:06,598
Peabody versus Danthorpe.

428
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:08,833
Son of a bitch.

429
00:16:08,869 --> 00:16:09,968
All right, smart guy.

430
00:16:10,003 --> 00:16:11,436
Now where are we gonna get
the money for the equity?

431
00:16:11,471 --> 00:16:13,121
I'll tell you where.
Sidwell and Gianopolous.

432
00:16:13,173 --> 00:16:14,589
<i>Is that another</i>
<i>straw man idea?</i>

433
00:16:14,624 --> 00:16:15,740
Because you'll never get
the two of them

434
00:16:15,776 --> 00:16:18,176
to go in on a deal together.
They hate each other.

435
00:16:18,178 --> 00:16:19,911
Oh, those two hating
each other is exactly

436
00:16:19,946 --> 00:16:22,046
what I'm counting on.

437
00:16:25,235 --> 00:16:27,285
<i>- Hey, Mom.</i>
- Oh, Rachel!

438
00:16:27,320 --> 00:16:28,753
<i>You're just in time.</i>

439
00:16:28,805 --> 00:16:31,022
The caterer dropped off
some samples.

440
00:16:31,074 --> 00:16:32,791
I was just about to try them,
but it'll be much more fun

441
00:16:32,826 --> 00:16:33,792
if we do this together.

442
00:16:33,844 --> 00:16:35,593
Okay, Mom,
but before you pout that.

443
00:16:35,629 --> 00:16:37,929
I don't think that
the crostini travels very well.

444
00:16:37,964 --> 00:16:39,931
Mom, please.

445
00:16:39,983 --> 00:16:42,100
I know that you have given this
a lot of thought,

446
00:16:42,135 --> 00:16:44,435
but I need to talk to you
about the size of the wedding.

447
00:16:44,471 --> 00:16:46,871
It's way too big.

448
00:16:46,907 --> 00:16:48,706
I have given this
a lot of thought,

449
00:16:48,742 --> 00:16:50,608
and 30 people
at a wedding

450
00:16:50,610 --> 00:16:52,844
isn't going to get
a chef like this.

451
00:16:52,879 --> 00:16:53,928
Right, but I'm not
having a wedding

452
00:16:53,964 --> 00:16:54,964
based on the chef,

453
00:16:55,015 --> 00:16:56,397
and I'm not here
to talk about the menu.

454
00:16:56,449 --> 00:17:00,118
I'm here to talk about
the guest list.

455
00:17:00,153 --> 00:17:01,820
Rachel, did I ever tell you
what your father did

456
00:17:01,822 --> 00:17:04,222
three weeks
before we got married?

457
00:17:04,257 --> 00:17:07,025
Bought two tickets to Bermuda
and said we're eloping.

458
00:17:07,060 --> 00:17:08,476
And he did that
because he didn't want

459
00:17:08,512 --> 00:17:09,994
to deal with my mother.

460
00:17:10,030 --> 00:17:12,230
But you know what stopped me?

461
00:17:12,265 --> 00:17:14,449
I knew that I would regret
doing that to my mom

462
00:17:14,501 --> 00:17:16,067
for the rest of my life.

463
00:17:16,102 --> 00:17:18,603
But I told you
this isn't about Mike,

464
00:17:18,655 --> 00:17:20,071
and it isn't
about eloping.

465
00:17:20,073 --> 00:17:22,106
This is just about
me not wanting to get married

466
00:17:22,142 --> 00:17:24,909
in front of hundreds of people
that I don't know.

467
00:17:24,945 --> 00:17:26,261
What's going on here, Rachel?

468
00:17:26,313 --> 00:17:27,553
<i>I'm telling you</i>
<i>what's going on.</i>

469
00:17:27,581 --> 00:17:28,613
You're just not hearing me.
I don't want this big

470
00:17:28,615 --> 00:17:29,948
of a wedding.

471
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:31,449
I'm hearing you,
but I know my own daughter,

472
00:17:31,484 --> 00:17:34,652
and there is something
that you're not telling me.

473
00:17:34,688 --> 00:17:35,870
Okay, Mom.

474
00:17:35,922 --> 00:17:37,255
Yes, there is something
that I'm not telling you,

475
00:17:37,257 --> 00:17:39,974
and that's because
it's really hard for me

476
00:17:40,010 --> 00:17:43,094
to say it.

477
00:17:43,146 --> 00:17:48,066
You keep thinking
that this is about Mike.

478
00:17:48,101 --> 00:17:49,267
Well, it's not.

479
00:17:49,269 --> 00:17:51,769
This is about you
not accepting that it's

480
00:17:51,771 --> 00:17:54,439
my wedding and it's not yours.

481
00:17:54,441 --> 00:17:55,690
Rachel.

482
00:17:55,742 --> 00:17:56,691
And if you can't
figure out a way to accept that,

483
00:17:56,743 --> 00:18:00,528
then I think maybe
we will have to elope.

484
00:18:08,339 --> 00:18:09,889
Jessica, can I talk to you
for a second?

485
00:18:09,925 --> 00:18:11,007
Can it wait till tomorrow?

486
00:18:11,059 --> 00:18:12,475
No.

487
00:18:12,511 --> 00:18:13,943
I think we should consider
promoting Jack Soloff

488
00:18:13,979 --> 00:18:15,245
to name partner.

489
00:18:15,280 --> 00:18:17,947
Are you crazy?

490
00:18:17,983 --> 00:18:19,232
Jessica, we are
under attack.

491
00:18:19,284 --> 00:18:20,583
And you're asking me
to reward our enemy.

