00:37:58,597 --> 00:38:01,965
he's gonna get you,
and nobody's gonna stop him.

988
00:38:02,017 --> 00:38:04,818
- Here's the thing, Harvey.

989
00:38:04,870 --> 00:38:08,805
Nobody doesn't
give a shit about money.

990
00:38:08,857 --> 00:38:10,974
Besides, in a week,
I'll be right back here

991
00:38:11,026 --> 00:38:14,444
picking off your clients
one by one.

992
00:38:14,496 --> 00:38:17,013
You want to stop me,
step down.

993
00:38:17,015 --> 00:38:19,382
- What?
- You resign,

994
00:38:19,418 --> 00:38:23,520
his money goes away.

995
00:38:23,555 --> 00:38:24,954
I knew it.

996
00:38:24,990 --> 00:38:27,190
You care about the people there,

997
00:38:27,225 --> 00:38:30,093
just like you cared about your
little brother way back when.

998
00:38:30,128 --> 00:38:31,995
- No way.

999
00:38:32,030 --> 00:38:32,979
No deal.

1000
00:38:33,031 --> 00:38:34,798
- Now, before you give me
an answer--

1001
00:38:34,833 --> 00:38:36,383
you came here tonight
because you know

1002
00:38:36,418 --> 00:38:38,234
you're gonna lose anyway.

1003
00:38:38,270 --> 00:38:40,153
So why not save whatever
poor sap it is

1004
00:38:40,188 --> 00:38:42,939
while you still can?

1005
00:38:42,974 --> 00:38:44,274
- Why should I believe
you would even live up

1006
00:38:44,309 --> 00:38:48,078
to your end of the bargain?

1007
00:38:48,113 --> 00:38:51,414
- Because I don't
give a shit about your war

1008
00:38:51,466 --> 00:38:53,316
with Daniel Hardman.

1009
00:38:53,351 --> 00:38:54,751
And I sure as hell
don't give a shit

1010
00:38:54,786 --> 00:38:57,604
about your firm.

1011
00:38:57,639 --> 00:39:00,340
All I want to do
is see you get down

1012
00:39:00,375 --> 00:39:03,460
on your knees
and say, "I quit."

1013
00:39:09,234 --> 00:39:10,734
- Trevor.

1014
00:39:10,769 --> 00:39:12,335
- Hey, Mike.

1015
00:39:16,041 --> 00:39:17,724
- Thanks for coming.
- Yeah, hey,

1016
00:39:17,759 --> 00:39:20,410
I'm glad you called.
- Yeah, me too.

1017
00:39:20,462 --> 00:39:22,512
- Listen, uh,
about the last time,

1018
00:39:22,547 --> 00:39:24,114
I said some things--

1019
00:39:24,149 --> 00:39:26,049
- Ah, we both
said some things.

1020
00:39:26,051 --> 00:39:29,753
But I did some things.
And I'm sorry.

1021
00:39:29,788 --> 00:39:33,623
- Well, uh, I have a way
you can make it up to me.

1022
00:39:33,658 --> 00:39:36,025
Come to my wedding.

1023
00:39:36,061 --> 00:39:37,961
- It means a lot to me
that you want me there,

1024
00:39:37,996 --> 00:39:39,262
but I'm sorry.

1025
00:39:39,297 --> 00:39:41,414
I can't.

1026
00:39:41,450 --> 00:39:42,966
- What do you mean you can't?

1027
00:39:43,018 --> 00:39:44,601
- Look, I'm married now,

1028
00:39:44,636 --> 00:39:47,070
and I promised my wife
that that part of my life

1029
00:39:47,105 --> 00:39:48,438
is behind me.

1030
00:39:48,490 --> 00:39:50,290
- What does that have to do
with you coming to my wedding?

1031
00:39:50,342 --> 00:39:52,575
- She didn't even want me
to meet you here.

1032
00:39:52,611 --> 00:39:56,446
Don't you get it?

1033
00:39:56,481 --> 00:39:58,381
You're breaking the law

1034
00:39:58,416 --> 00:39:59,949
every day.

1035
00:39:59,985 --> 00:40:01,384
- You're judging me?
- No.

1036
00:40:01,419 --> 00:40:03,820
I'm not judging you.

1037
00:40:03,872 --> 00:40:05,789
Nothing would make me happier
than to raise a glass

1038
00:40:05,791 --> 00:40:07,841
to your new life,

1039
00:40:07,876 --> 00:40:10,326
but I can't.

1040
00:40:10,362 --> 00:40:11,362
And you shouldn't either.

1041
00:40:11,396 --> 00:40:12,595
- Oh, so now
I shouldn't get married?

1042
00:40:12,631 --> 00:40:13,930
- No, I'm saying
you should quit.

1043
00:40:16,601 --> 00:40:17,734
Oh, okay.

1044
00:40:17,769 --> 00:40:20,136
Well, thank you
for the advice, Trevor.

1045
00:40:20,172 --> 00:40:22,372
But I don't think
I'm going to do that.

1046
00:40:22,424 --> 00:40:25,942
- Michael, the longer you go,

1047
00:40:25,977 --> 00:40:28,845
the less the money matters.

1048
00:40:28,880 --> 00:40:31,114
The food doesn't taste as good.

1049
00:40:31,149 --> 00:40:32,215
The car isn't fast enough.

1050
00:40:32,217 --> 00:40:34,217
The view isn't high enough.

1051
00:40:34,269 --> 00:40:36,136
And finally you realize

1052
00:40:36,188 --> 00:40:37,687
that you would trade it all in

1053
00:40:37,722 --> 00:40:41,391
for one night of going to bed

1054
00:40:41,443 --> 00:40:43,026
where you don't have to worry,

1055
00:40:43,061 --> 00:40:46,146
"When are they gonna
come for me?"

1056
00:40:46,198 --> 00:40:48,231
- You almost got caught,
didn't you?

1057
00:40:48,233 --> 00:40:52,485
- No, I didn't.
I just couldn't take it anymore.

1058
00:40:52,537 --> 00:40:54,571
So finally, I went
to talk to someone.

1059
00:40:54,623 --> 00:40:56,623
- Who?

1060
00:40:56,658 --> 00:40:58,074
- You know who.

1061
00:41:01,379 --> 00:41:03,163
I gotta go.

1062
00:41:07,552 --> 00:41:09,052
Take care, Michael.

1063
